          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636392611101-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636392611101-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636392611101-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the veg is in the oven, boil half a kettle</p><p>Dice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your<strong> spicy tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636392615656-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636392615656-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636392615656-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636392615656-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636392615656-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced tomato</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes have broken down</p><p>Add the <strong>spicy tomato stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further or until thickened – this is your <strong>bravas sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636392625784-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636392625784-x400.jpg",
